headline: Details Are Scant, but Australia’s Target Is Clear in First Foreign-Meddling Arrest
text: MELBOURNE, Australia — When the Australian authorities announced the first arrest under the country’s new foreign interference laws this week, they said little about what the suspect was accused of doing, and nothing at all about the country on whose behalf he was believed to have worked.
snippet: The suspect, who has been active in Chinese-Australian groups, was charged under laws against foreign interference that were seen as a response to China.
